[HEADING] About us
The Ohio State University
Obtaining a master's degree from Ohio State's Material Science and Engineering graduate program can be very rewarding, both for your career and for you personally. The challenges you'll tackle and the mentoring you'll receive will prepare you to take your place at the cutting edge of technology.
Our highly-ranked, tight-knit department lends a small-school feel with all the advantages that a large research university can offer. A diverse student body brings together people from many cultural and academic backgrounds providing an innovative environment. Over $17 million per year in research funding is added to this mix to explore the field of materials science.
MSE highlights:
Access to extensive world-class research facilities, both in-house and university wide
Optional Practical Training (OPT)
International graduates of this major are eligible per the Department of Homeland Security to apply for up to three (3) years of work permission in the United States after graduation. See the Office of International Affairs website for more eligibility requirements.

[HEADING] The Graduate School
[HEADING] Questions?
[HEADING] Tiles
[HEADING] Points of Pride
Prospective MSE or WE graduate students
For those prospective students seeking a Master's and/or PhD in the fields of Materials Science and Engineering or Welding Engineering. Applicants must hold a Bachelor's degree or its equivalent prior to the proposed semester of admission. Includes details on application requirements & procedures, financial aid, degree requirements, and more.
Learn more about the Online Learning MS in Welding Engineering
The Welding Engineering graduate program is proud to offer a 100% online Master of Science in Welding Engineering for students with a Bachelor of Science in Engineering or allied field who are seeking to expand their knowledge. Our online distance education program allows students from around the world to access our courses with no on-campus residency requirement. Additionally, these courses are billed at in-state rates regardless of the student's citizenship or location.
Newly admitted MSE and WE graduate students
Includes instructions on how to prepare for arrival on campus, housing information, details on student health insurance, and other useful pre-arrival matters.
Enrolled MSE and WE graduate students
For currently enrolled graduate students in the MSE and WE programs at Ohio State. Includes information on the three degree tracks within each program (MSE and WE), financial aid, courses, seminar schedule, graduation procedures, employment, BS/MS program, and more.
The OSU Graduate School
Provides information on programs and degrees, resources for grad students, and much more.
Please contact Mark Cooper, Graduate Studies Coordinator, should you have questions about our graduate programs in MSE and WE.
